1. User Interface (UI) Design
Home Page: A simple and intuitive interface where users can select the currency they want to buy or sell.
Currency Selection: Dropdown menus or a search bar for selecting currencies.
Exchange Offers: A section displaying current offers from other users, including the currency and the exchange rate.
Calculator: An interactive tool for users to calculate their potential profit or loss from a currency exchange.
2. User Registration and Profile Management
Allow users to create accounts to manage their offers and transactions.
Profile pages where users can view their transaction history and current offers.
3. Currency Exchange Functionality
Posting Offers: Users should be able to post offers indicating the currency they have and the exchange rate they are willing to accept

Objective:
Develop a responsive, SEO-optimized Tailwind CSS website/landing page/funnel that serves as an informational and lead generation platform for a local microgreens farm based in Perth, Western Australia.

Target Audience:
Local Perth residents interested in healthy eating, restaurants and chefs sourcing fresh produce, and health-conscious individuals seeking nutritional supplements through microgreens.

Business Goals:
Educate the public about the benefits of microgreens.
Generate leads for the business through newsletter sign-ups, form submissions, and purchase inquiries.
Establish a strong local presence and brand recognition.
Drive conversions in the form of microgreens pre-orders, subscriptions, or purchases.
